contentrichtext.text: {{Infobox Protected area | name = Mount Colosseum National Park | iucn_category = II | photo = | photo_caption = | location = [[Central Queensland]] | nearest_city = [[Gladstone, Queensland|Gladstone]] | lat_d = 24 | lat_m = 24 | lat_s = 33 | lat_NS = S | long_d = 151 | long_m = 35 | long_s = 01 | long_EW = E | map = Australia | map_width = 250 | region = AU-QLD | area = {{convert|8.4|km2|sqmi|0}} | established = 1977 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = [[Queensland Parks and Wildlife Service]] | url = http://www.derm.qld.gov.au/parks/mount-colosseum/index.html }} '''Mount Colosseum''' is a national park in [[Central Queensland]], [[Australia]], {{convert|370|km|mi|0}} northwest of [[Brisbane]] and about {{convert|6|km|mi|0}} south of the town of [[Miriam Vale, Queensland|Miriam Vale]]. Mount Colosseum is a [[volcanic dome]] and is the dominant feature on the skyline of the area.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://easyfindguide.com.au/centralqld/listing.asp?Biz_ID=79903&sub=4037&guide=278|title=Central Queensland Easy Guide|year=2010|accessdate=2010-06-19}}</ref> The dome rises to an elevation of {{convert|470|m|ft|0}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.experiencequeensland.com/iss/uk/regions/central-queensland/gladstone.cfm|title=Queensland , Australia - Regions|year=2010|accessdate=2010-06-19}}</ref> and is sparsely covered in [[hoop pine]]s, while the dry [[rainforest]] below contains [[ironbark]]s and [[bloodwood]]s. The park is undeveloped and has no facilities available for visitors. No [[camping]] is allowed in the park and no walking tracks exist within the park. ==See also== {{Portal|Queensland}} * [[Protected areas of Queensland]] == References == {{reflist}} {{National Parks of Queensland}} [[Category:National parks of Queensland]] [[Category:Protected areas established in 1977]] [[Category:Central Queensland]] {{Queensland-national-park-stub}}
